reviews.text: Really disappointed with this place, it has gone downhill after changing management from a Food Republic. The ramen place was really disappointing (and slow), and unapologetic in relying on small print print to deny me a drink for my set lunch. The Pepper Lunch portion has shrunk even further. The shaved ice dessert was compacted as if they were making a snowball with some canned pineapple slices stuck on the side and no flavour to the ice. Suffice to say that I won't be returning
Good range but pay extra $10 with food for a discounted drink
Good selection of food to choose from. Seating as usual can be an issue during peak times. The place was kept clean throughout which is good

The play ground used to be the best place for my family to play and enjoy foods, unfortunately the management of the play ground is the "safest" in the world. They always shut down the play ground even a tiny grey cloud in the sky, (shut down for a while day)
The food that i try so delicious. Many good food in here

reviews.text: 位於新世紀廣場樓上，有不同款式的食品可以選擇，價錢比較經濟，不過因為每間小店也有獨立廚房，所以油煙較多，空氣比較混濁及冷氣不足。
設有各國各式各樣的料理，適合各任人仕的食堂，整體整潔有条亂。
位處於旺角東站Moko三楼的food court，東南亞中西美食都有，梗有一樣啱心水。
旺角區嚟講價錢合理，食物方面因為只是食早餐沒有大問題， 下次要嚟試下呢個法式華園農夫包因賣相都好似幾得咁,而午餐及晚餐就未嘗試過， 但因為在Food court 内隔離的小店很大油煙。
涮香菜園食品好差，好難食，小辣也辣到令人身體不適，鼻水眼水齊流，簡直貼錢買難受!
